    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-06-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-06-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="138" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d138">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-06-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 25,
                            1890</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 542.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 1113 of the 5th
                        ultimo, relative to the claim of the American citizen Louis McCaslin against
                        China for injuries caused by the wrongful closing of a bridge of boats at
                        Ningpo, April 29, 1888. Your note in the case of the 5th ultimo is
                        approved.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
